Description:
"4 BEDROOMS, HUNT CLUB"
'(217463) Built in 2010 this family home is in a great location with the Cranbourne East school at the end of the street and only a short walk to Casey Grammar school.
This four bedroom home is made with family space in mind, comprising of a huge master bedroom with walk in robe and full ensuite. The remaining three bedrooms have robes and generous sizing for your growing family needs.
This home is equipped with ducted-heating throughout a large family living and separate dining area and has a second separate lounge area located towards the front of the house to cater for larger families. The kitchen has a stainless steel under bench oven and gas cook-top and plenty of space for all your cooking needs.
All this indoor space is accompanied by a large outdoor entertaining area finished by a merbau decking pergola patio area, and a double garage under roof-line with auto door and most important a rear access door for cars boat or trailer to the back yard.
Call Frank Barrett for all enquiries.'
WE ARE OPEN SUNDAYS

Description:
DON'T MISS OUT ON THIS BEAUTY!
Loved and cared for, this fine family home allows the lucky new purchaser to move in with nothing to do! The property itself is nestled on a care free block allowing you to spend more time enjoying the house and less time maintaining it.
A quality built home featuring 3 spacious bedrooms. The master suite is complete with a WIR and a full ensuite with an oversized shower, whilst bedrooms 2 and 3 all have double robes and are in close proximity to the family bathroom with separate bath and shower facilities.
The hostess kitchen is the central hub of the home and offers ample cupboard space with tiled splash back. Quality appliances includes dishwasher, 4-burner gas hot plate, oven and range hood. Added internal extras include tiled flooring, neutral tones, plus RC/SS air conditioning.
Step outside and be greeted by a nicely manicured front yard which adds to the overall street appeal. The coloured concreted driveway that leads to the remote single garage with internal/rear walkway access!
With the spacious living zone and the main focal point being the under roofline alfresco, With the Summer months upon us, this is the perfect place to enjoy the company of family and friends with a traditional Aussie BBQ! You will have no issues in entertaining year in year out!
Bonus external features include a brick facade, porched entry and private rear entertaining area.
Within a short drive to freeway access and all amenities located in the townships of Berwick, Clyde and Cranbourne, this sensational opportunity is only minutes away from the popular Clyde Primary School, One Early Education Group offering long day care and kindergarten facilities, Casey RACE Recreation & Aquatic Centre and Casey Indoor Sports Centre! With additional shopping precincts in Pasadena, Selandra Rise/Cascades on Clyde and The Hunt Club local amenities are always going to be close by, whilst the recently revamped Cranbourne Park Shopping Centre offers an abundance of cafes and restaurants! Don't forget the proposed Cranbourne East train station, or the existing ones situated right throughout the South East!
If you want your family to have easy access to the very best in entertainment, education and recreation, this is the perfect location for you!
BOOK AN INSPECTION TODAY, IT MAY BE GONE TOMORROW! - *PHOTO ID REQUIRED AT OPEN FOR INSPECTIONS*! You can view with confidence that vendors will sell within the range with favourable conditions.

Description:
FAMILY LIVING IN THE HUNT CLUB
CRANBOURNE EAST: If you are looking for the perfect family home then look no further than this beautifully presented four-bedroom home in the highly sort after Hunt Club Estate.
A wonderfully versatile floor plan arrangement is introduced by the separate lounge area which flows through to the relaxed family domain. The contemporary kitchen which overlooks the dining and family area consists of Caesar stone bench tops and high-end appliances. Those needing additional space will be greatly pleased with the separate yet adjoining rumpus room.
Flowing out from the main living zone is the alfresco area which is ideal for entertaining family and friends all while watching the kids play in the back yard.
Separated by a rear hallway are three bedrooms which are all generous in proportion with double door robes. The over-size master suite is set apart at the front of the home which offers added privacy. Featuring en suite with spa and double vanities, a large walk in robe and its own separate study room.
The Hunt Club is a multi-award-winning estate offering numerous parks, Hunt Club Wetlands, walking and bicycle paths as well as a complete range of childcare, primary (Cranbourne East Primary) and secondary schools (Cranbourne East Secondary College). Recycled water, high speed broadband and environmentally friendly designs are all part of the estate.
Added internal and external features include;
* Approximately 34 sq under roof line
* Approximately 576 sqm land
* Four bed rooms plus study
* Master retreat suite with large floor space
* Master en suite with spa bath, double vanities, separate toilet and WIR
* Three living areas and theatre room (rumpus)
* Double glazed windows
* Beautiful Gas fire place natural looking with remote control
* 40mm Ceasar stone island benchtop, 20mm stone bench top to kitchen and bathrooms
* 900 mm five burner gas cook top
* 900 mm oven
* Canopy range hood and glass flashback
* Butler pantry to the kitchen
* Under mount sink
* Ducted heating
* Evaporative cooling
* Spa bath in en suite
* Master with walk in robe
* Solar electricity
* Solar assisted hot water
* Theatre system wiring installed
* Fibre optic wiring being installed
* Double garage
* Internal access to garage
* Remote roller door
* 3 x 3 m Shed
* 3 capped gas point to outside gas line
* Plantation shutters
* Security alarm system
* Big Alfresco with Merbau decking
* 4 leaf timber bi-fold doors to family/alfresco
* Veggie patches
* Down lights throughout
* Fully landscaped low maintenance gardens
* Concrete pavers all around the house
- Archers Field Drive bus stop (898) is approximately six minutes' walk away from the house
- Cranbourne East Primary School is approximately two minutes' walk away from the house
- Cranbourne East Secondary School is approximately seven minutes' walk away from the house
- The Casey Complex is approximately four minutes' drive away from the house
- Cranbourne Park shopping centre is approximately seven minutes' drive away from the house

Description:
TAKE A STEP FORWARD IN STYLE
CLOSING DATE SALE: 22nd December @ 7pm
(Unless Sold Prior)
This single-storey "Simonds - New Living 2014 Range" built dream won't just elevate your home living, it'll also lift your lifestyle.
Behind the imposing façade of this four-bedroom plus study/bedroom house is plenty to recommend, and a family-friendly location only adds to the appeal. Open plan living area featuring quality Highland Oak timber floorboards flowing beautifully to the contemporary design kitchen.
The spacious floorplan is well-balanced and offers large casual and formal shared areas, providing ample room for retreat or bringing family and friends together.
At the heart of the home is an open-plan space, where plenty of natural light and bi-fold doors that lead to a covered pergola area create a lovely, relaxed ambience and complimented by a private, landscaped courtyard.
And back inside, the kitchen is likely to delight home chefs, too. It anchors the open-plan hub and is adorned with laminate benchtops and contemporary pendant lighting that illuminates the long island bench.
Technika appliances help ensure optimal utility, as does the butler's pantry and abundance of cabinet space.
As well as a rumpus room and formal sitting room with ducted heating throughout and an ensuite with walk-in-robe can be found at the front of the house. It's joined by three others with built-in-robes plus a study which can be transformed into the fifth bedroom, all are carpeted and complimented with a separate bathroom and toilet. A double remote-control lockup garage with internal entry. Don't miss out on this one. Enquire today.
Please contact Tommy 0431 644 889 or Corey 0417 311 491 for more information.
*Please Note* - Biggin & Scott Greater Dandenong may refuse to provide further information about the property should you prefer not to disclose your Full Contact Details including Phone Number. Photo ID is required upon entering the property.

Description:
Approx 39 squares on 772 sqm block
HUNT CLUB SUPER HOME ---- EPIC, mind blowing, stunning & luxurious are just some of the words to describe 18 Monmouth road, Cranbourne east. This amazing HOME sits on a massive 772sqm allotment and with more than enough room for your family and your toys and your hobbies.
The interior is modern, elegant and relaxing. When you step onto the property, you are welcomed by its beautifully landscaped gardens & massive driveway. At the entrance you are welcomed by a decked staircase that leads to the front door and onto a journey through this gorgeous home. Starting at the sleeping quarters with an enormous master bedroom with its own private alfresco, huge WIR & ensuite with double vanities, stone benches, & oversized shower, and another 3 large bedrooms all with BIRs, and a central bathroom.
With 3 SEPERATE LIVING AREAS on offer, starting off with a formal lounge for your guests, and then onto a huge family living and dining area, as well as an extra rumpus/theatre room for the kids, all the living space is centered by an amazing kitchen consisting of plenty of cupboard and bench space, stone benches, dishwasher, 900mm oven, island bench, huge walk in pantry and much more.
The outdoor in this home offers 3 SEPARATE ALFRESCOS, one in the master, one off the family living area, and a 3rd enormous fully enclosed decked alfresco overlooking the big backyard area that this home has on offer. In addition to all this there is side access for other vehicles.
The property is situated in the sought after Hunt Club Estate in Cranbourne East, in a quiet location, and only a stone's throw from Cranbourne East schools and childcare, parks, wetlands, this amazing home with style and distinction at the forefront of design.
This home is an absolute must see, don't miss out of this unreal opportunity for you and your family, for inspections or any questions please contact MINA SAAD on 0401 053 553.
FEATIURES:
- 4 bedrooms + study, large master with full ensuite and large WIR.
- 3 separate living areas, lounge, family living area & rumpus.
- 3 separate alfresco areas.
- Huge kitchen plenty of cupboard and bench space, stone benches, dishwasher, island bench, walk in pantry.
- Extras include, high ceilings, cooling & heating, landscaped gardens back & front, side access. Big backyard and much more.

Description:
Premium Living
Built in 2014 and in good as new condition, this high spec home exudes quality and elegance throughout. Located in the heart of numerous school zones, close to the Cranbourne High Street Shopping Precinct and the fantastic recreational amenities of Casey Fields, this home provides the perfect setting for the whole family.
Set to impress from the start, youâ??ll love the high ceilings, light timber style flooring and modern design throughout. In the heart of the home, an open plan kitchen, meals and family room create the perfect environment for casual family living. An additional rumpus provides a valuable second living space which enjoys a vista onto the neatly landscaped gardens. The generous kitchen includes stainless steel appliances; 5 burner gas cook top, 900mm wide electric oven and dishwasher as well as contemporary cabinetry, glass splashback and Caesarstone benchtops.
Also on offer are four bedrooms and two bathrooms; at the front of the home the master bedroom with walk in robe and full ensuite with extra wide shower. The three rear bedrooms have built in robes and are nearby a central bathroom with separate WC. Accompanied by a study the layout provides an ideal zone for kids and teenagers. The interiors are concludes with stylish plantation shutters, ducted heating, a split system air conditioner, downlights, ceiling fans and a handy ducted vacuum system.
The outdoor area provides a good size, neatly landscaped backyard with storage shed and secure parking via the double garage with rear and internal access. The stand-out feature of the backyard, however, is the wrap around alfresco with timber decking. Family gatherings this summer will be an absolute hit with this brilliant entertainers delight!
Immaculate both inside and out, you wonâ??t find a better home on the market! Call today to avoid missing out on this home with the whole package.
